</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,221,452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
I agree with this opinion and, because no 
<typeStatus box="[650,734,290,313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">neotype</typeStatus>
has been formerly designated by Alonso-Zarazaga, I designate a specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[289,381,325,348]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Eutrichapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vorax">
<emphasis box="[289,381,325,348]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">E. vorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[459,543,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[581,723,325,348]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosellum">
<emphasis box="[581,723,325,348]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">A. pilosellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is a male (fig. 
<number box="[919,933,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" value="4.0">4</number>
) labelled: Frankenhausen Kyff., 
<date box="[1289,1397,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" value="1963-08-19">
<number box="[1289,1338,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" value="19.8">19.8</number>
. 
<number box="[1341,1397,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" value="1963.0">1963</number>
